{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/Graphs\/documentation\/Graphs"]]},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/graphs\/applymanybodyforce(to:strength:mindistance:)"]}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"applyManyBodyForce","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"to","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"state","kind":"internalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"inout","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Graphs\/documentation\/Graphs\/SimulationState","text":"SimulationState","preciseIdentifier":"s:6Graphs15SimulationStateV","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"text":"strength","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Sf","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Float"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"minDistance"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Float","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sf"},{"kind":"text","text":" = 1.0)"}],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"parameters":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The simulation state to modify. Velocities are updated in place.","type":"text"}]}],"name":"state"},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The force strength. Negative values cause repulsion (typical),"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"positive values cause attraction. Default is set via "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Graphs\/documentation\/Graphs\/SimulationConfig","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}],"name":"strength"},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Minimum distance for force calculations. Prevents extremely"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"large forces when nodes are very close. Defaults to 1.0."}]}],"name":"minDistance"}],"kind":"parameters"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","anchor":"discussion","level":2,"text":"Discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This force causes nodes to repel (with negative strength) or attract (with","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"positive strength) each other. It’s the primary force that spreads nodes apart","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"in a force-directed layout.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Overview","level":2,"text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The force follows an inverse-square law similar to gravity or electrostatic","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"force. The magnitude scales with the simulation’s alpha value, causing the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"force to decrease as the simulation settles.","type":"text"}]},{"level":2,"anchor":"Complexity","text":"Complexity","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"O(N²) where N is the number of nodes. This implementation is optimized for"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"small graphs (< 500 nodes) with a simple memory access pattern.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Coincident-Nodes","level":2,"text":"Coincident Nodes","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"When two nodes occupy the same position, a small random offset (“jiggle”)","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"is applied to break the symmetry and allow the nodes to separate."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Example","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Example"},{"code":["applyManyBodyForce(to: &state, strength: -30.0)"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"}]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"sections":[],"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"Graphs"}],"roleHeading":"Function","externalID":"s:6Graphs18applyManyBodyForce2to8strength11minDistanceyAA15SimulationStateVz_S2ft